<br>
1)  Make Wizard DPS HIGHER than that of a rogue or a monk.  And lets face it, Verant is NOT going to do this.<br>
<br>
2)  Introduce several melee proof mobs in the game.<br>
<br>
3)  Break from the Vision and give Wizards some useful utility spells.  My personal suggestion would be a breeze type spell that can be cast on other people.<br>
<br>
Lets pretend for a second that Verant increases Wizards DPS to be the same as a rogue or a monk.  Guess what, most groups will STILL want the rogue or monk over a wizard.  Why?  Because they can tank, have more hps, have higher AC, can taunt, and you don't have to worry about their mana supply.  Wizards cannot take a hit and will crumple like a piece of paper when high level mobs aggro on them.  So even if they do the same DPS as a monk, who really cares?  I'd still rather have a monk!<br>
<br>
Most groups don't care about evac.  Root and snare are easily obtainable from other classes.  Wizards have nothing to offer a group except damage, which is easily obtained from other classes.<br>
<br>
Now if you give a Wizard a breeze type spell that stacks with enchanter mana buffs, many groups would consider taking a wizard who was lfg, especially if no enchanter was available.<br>
<br>
This would not be unfair.  Enchanters can nuke, just like wizards (though not as good as a wizard).  Why shouldn't wizards be able to cast mana regen, like enchanters (though not as good as an enchanter)?  It fits with our class.  Wizards are totally dependent on mana, after all.<br>
<br>
This would also help the DPS situation.<br>
<br>
wgbutler<br>
