<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
WGBulter  I believe you have good intentions at heart, so I will respond with my ideas.<br>
<br>
1) I believe has everything to do with time frame.  Wizards have always been and always will be a burst class.  Meaning we do our damage in quick bursts then we are out of the battle for a while.  I do agree with the idea of having our Burst DPS greatly increased to be more on par with Melee.  I have seen posts where ppl estimate Rogue dps at 115.  I have no problem entertaining the idea of Wizards doing 300-350 dps in the first 2 mins of a battle.  as long as the wizard is out of the battle for the next couple of minutes.  I have also seen posts where wizards have stated they have reached 300 dps.  But that was at level 60 with a LARGE number of AA points, and using a very specialized spell (banes).  I would like to see this scaled back and made apporpriate to each level. <br>
<br>
2)  Melee proof mobs would be nice but at this stage in the game very inpracticle.  Because of the way taunt/hate works.  Melees only generate hate when they hit a mob.  Therefore a melee proof mob would be ping ponging around killing all the casters.<br>
<br>
3)  Honestly I don't like the idea of buffing.  I would rather leave that to the shaman, druids and clerics.  I buffing as a bigger headache than TLs, and ports.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Moderator</font></td></tr></table><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Verant's #1 Fanboy</font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 3817<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/24/02 4:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Balance</span><hr size=1> 1. We'll never be higher than a Rogue or a Monk, nor should we be.  They are doing in the pure melee field what we're supposed to be doing in the pure caster field.  We need to be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> on par</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> with them in the short and semi-long run.  Sustained damage is the biggest problems Wizards face.<br>
<br>
2. The only way I can think of to create a melee proof mob is to build a mob that does nothing but cast, is rooted, and is invulnerable to melee attacks.  Personally I think that would be an increddibly boring fight... I know I wouldn't want to participate it in.  The more reasonable solution is a melee resistant mobs, these mobs have been in the game since Kunark and we're seeing them more than ever in Luclin.  These mobs do ATK debuff curses, AE slows, have high AC, etc etc.  These are the mobs that you need your casters (specifically Wizards) on and everytime you go up against these mobs a Wizard will be the top damage dealer for the fight.<br>
<br>
3. We have translocates and ports and that's all we need really.  I personally picked a Wizard because buffing sucks. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   People have already posted several times about how much they despise Spell Shield so I doubt buffs (especially ones that would be wanted by anyone who couldn't find an Enchanter) would be welcome.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lets pretend for a second that Verant increases Wizards DPS to be the same as a rogue or a monk. Guess what, most groups will STILL want the rogue or monk over a wizard. Why? Because they can tank, have more hps, have higher AC, can taunt, and you don't have to worry about their mana supply. Wizards cannot take a hit and will crumple like a piece of paper when high level mobs aggro on them. So even if they do the same DPS as a monk, who really cares? I'd still rather have a monk!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Well, first of all neither Monks nor Rogues have a taunt ability.  Secondly, a Monk can make a decent tank but Rogues can't tank mobs efficiently unless they are well equipped.  Furthermore when they're not using their backstab ability you'll see a dramatic drop in their DPS.  Our job is to avoid agro and maximize damage, this is why we have concussion.  A Wizard should avoid agro at all turns.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Most groups don't care about evac. Root and snare are easily obtainable from other classes. Wizards have nothing to offer a group except damage, which is easily obtained from other classes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Why let them get someone else for snare and root to take up your EXP when you can do both and contribute damage as well as evacs (which people highly under-rate <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )? <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> This would not be unfair. Enchanters can nuke, just like wizards (though not as good as a wizard). Why shouldn't wizards be able to cast mana regen, like enchanters (though not as good as an enchanter)? It fits with our class. Wizards are totally dependent on mana, after all.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Every casting class in EQ can nuke, so this isn't a very good argument.  We should also get Superior Healing because Clerics can nuke just like Wizards.  And we should get pets because Mages can nuke like Wizards.  See what I mean?  Hehe.  It really doesn't fit our class either... Warriors are dependent on HP, should they have heals?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The best solution IMO would be to give us better sustained damage over time as that really is our biggest problem. <p><br>
