EDIT:  me (60 wiz) and a 55 wiz got the xp kill on Rhag and that was over a group with 60 monk/war/rogue/ranger using epic's and/or primals. <p><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76296">Izual Adept</a><BR>60 Sorcerer<BR>Xev<BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/orderofdraconis/Izualsig.gif></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uizualxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izual Xev</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/27/02 3:38:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1601<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/02 9:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: short term</span><hr size=1> I hate to say it, but it all comes back to DPS. How much each does over duration. If a Monk can sustain 60 DPS over a ten minute duration, a Wizard (if that's who we're compared with) should do roughly the same DPS.<br>
Now how they do their damage over that ten minutes isn't important, it's that they are equal in tens of damage over the same amount of time.<br>
Obviously, Wizards were designed around burst damage; high ammounts of damage in short amounts of time. So of those 10 minutes, should a wizard have done all of their damage in 3 minutes, and it takes the Monk an additional 7 minutes to do the same damage? <br>
That's what it comes down to. How much time should each class do their damage, and still remain balanced with each other.<br>
<br>
The problem with &quot;melee-resistant&quot; mobs is the same problem as magic resistant mobs. When you use a tool like these, you're leaving alot of classes out of the picture. Casters hate magic immune mobs. They can't do anything but sit there the entire fight.<br>
Melee classes feel the same way about these &quot;melee-resistant&quot; mobs. The thing is, they're still required to do these encounters. If there were no one to tank these mobs, the casters wouldn't be able to do their damage, and those mobs would be hard as hell.<br>
I can totally see both points of view. A melee class isn't going to want to raid a mob on a regular occasion where all they're doing is getting healed while the casters do all the damage. They strive for kill shots, and so do we.<br>
