<br>
<br>
If melees had to wait half a second IN ADDITION to their delay on their weapon for every swing of their weapon, they would be rather upset.  But I don't see wizards getting upset about our ability to burn through our mana bar being intentionally nerfed by design.<br>
<br>
We have cast time, recovery time, recast delay.  Melees get an instant attack with the delay that gets reduced by haste items.  Nothing eliminates the recovery time.  We even have a bug in the game where if we cast our level 1 and 4 spells, we often get a message saying we can't cast yet?  WTF?  If we want to blow all our mana as quickly as we can, why the recovery time that's static and doesn't take any spell data into account?<br>
