Level 60 Wizard<br>
The First Seal<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>(Title left blank)</span><br>  Posts: 5063<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/31/02 11:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> damage</span><hr size=1> OK let's make something pretty clear right here.  At present we already DO do about 10 minutes melee damage in 3 minutes or so.  If I emptied my entire mana pool without resists into a monster, it would be a smoking crater to the tune of around 11k damage.  That's a lot of hitting a monster, especially at 20-30 a pop like most melee average.<br>
<br>
The problem is that we can't do that, not in any real part of the game, not against anything that matters.  The trinity of control (aggro, mana use, and time) keeps us from dumping this on each monster, or we really would be overpowered.  But if you look at what we can do now, even with Clarity 2, I can only average about 2-3 blasts per fight, which limits my damage output significantly.  The need to wait for aggro control and the speed monsters die prevents me from nuking much more than that, even assuming my mana was coming back much faster.<br>
<br>
In other words, the things that need to change aren't the raw damage output, its my ability to apply my damage.  It really doesn't have to be much of a change, just a few small nudges in damage numbers.  Damage numbers don't need to change except in a few specific areas and levels. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 513<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/31/02 10:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: damage</span><hr size=1> Grim, we obviously can't do this if our damage output over time is that low.<br>
<br>
If we cast 2 times per mob, we still end up being out damaged by the melees.  If we dump our mana, the time it takes to get that mana back should allow melees to catch up to us, not outdamage us.  That's the balance problem.<br>
<br>
To look at balance again, let's use Elnerick's for this example.  1890 damage in 7.5 seconds for 525 mana.  Now, how long does it take to regain that 525 mana?  If that time exceeds the ability of melees to do 1890 damage, then they will outdamage us over time.  It's not the delivery time(7.5 seconds), it's deliver time plus recovery time.  <br>
<br>
Since Elnerick's is as rare as the good melee drops off most uber mobs(not the best stuff like in ST), we can see that this is the balance that needs to be struck.  And since it's clear that melees CAN exceed the 1890 damage mark, or even 3780 crit with disciplines, that's why the class needs to be properly balanced.  Focus items MAY do it, but until we know what the top end is on focus effects, we will need to wait and see.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 60 Wizard<br>
The First Seal<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uminkazaubermaus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minka Zaubermaus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/3/02 5:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: damage</span><hr size=1> Wizards suck in lower levels, thats well known and not worth to talk about it once again. If you make it up to lvl 60 (and beyond that with AA skills) you will see its worth the effort.<br>
<br>
I guess we all agree that the melees are only that good if their equipment is that good. Fast weapons, Haste, additional buffs or effects on weapons etc. With the appropiate classes in the group (on raids you nearly allways have at least one of each class for buffing purposes, so I wont talk about this) they can do their maxed damage. What about Wizards? Nearly the same. With C3 (and in some cases with additional Manasongs) your mana recovers fast... add SCM (less mana per nuke), SCF (crits), add MC and FT Items (which you CAN get in a good guild, even up to FT15 when you give your guild some time to get enough that you can obtain some yourself) you are fine. Add Nukeitems like Robe of Invocation and you are set. All you need now is a good taunter to hold the aggro (the better he taunts including procs of weapons or spells) the earlier you can start nuking (and if you nuke - concussion - nuke - concussion etc) you can do a lot of damage without getting aggro. Now add Bracer-earring, you will do more damage/avoid aggro. Once able to do some more AA-Skills, add the loweraggro skill and the problems with aggro become less again. So you see in the long run (if you make it till here that is) you can do a lot of damage in short time without endless recovery. <br>
<br>
I had a hard time to level up till lvl 60. And to get the AApoints (still working on it and will do for a long time I guess), but I dont hide behind any melee any longer. I am curious as hell what focus items VI will offer, and I will work on getting those with the most effective use for wizards. You can work on your char the same way a melee has to work on his, and you CAN be a VERY good class for groups, even xp groups not doing ae, as long as you are skilled enough to play your wizard. Just stop whining and prove it to your group. Dont overnuke, dont whine or compete with other classes (and bump your whole mana in one mob when its not necessary), use your power and it will work.<br>
